Christina Pitt Police have killed two suspects in a shootout. (File, Nielen Bottomley, News24) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Investigations are underway after two robbery suspects were killed during a shootout with police in Ballito, near Durban, in the early hours of Tuesday morning. Police traced the suspects to a house in Piesang River, Inanda, after five suspects robbed a Ballito jewellery store at gunpoint on Monday. "As the police officers approached the house, the suspects opened fire at them," police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said. "Two suspects were fatally wounded during the exchange of gunfire. Two unlicensed firearms and ammunition were seized from the deceased suspects." A case of armed robbery was registered at the Umhlali police station for further investigation. "The investigation into the armed robbery at Ballito continues and attempts are underway to trace and arrest the remaining suspects involved in the incident," Mbhele said. "The firearms will be subjected to ballistic tests to establish if they were used in the commission of any crimes in the country." KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  